new study highlights urban climate change risks from hue city kèm dịch tiếng việt institute for_social and_environmental transition-international new study highlights urban climate change risks from hue city kèm dịch tiếng việt posted by iset-international in acccrn iset-vietnam m-brace photo1 by huy_nguyen iset-vietnam photo2 by tho ng iset-vietnam climate_change and_planned urban expansion in floodways will compound flood risk for the city of_hue according to a_new climate vulnerability assessment implemented by the thua thien hue province climate change working_group and iset-vietnam under the m-brace program the assessment highlights the importance of_planning future urban development on the basis of_solid assessments of_future climate risks when the b2 scenario is applied there are clear risks of_reduced rainfall in the dry season and_also 30 more rainfall in the flood season as worrying as these findings are the assessment points out that historical precipitation records demonstrate that hue has moved beyond the b2 scenario and_that these are underestimates of_the full level of_water-related climate threats there are also concerns that existing infrastructure drainage in urban areas and_upstream flood protection are not able to cope with current rainfall pressures let alone future climate threats the working group presented its findings to committee members provincial department leaders and_academics at shared learning dialogue sponsored by usaid on march th in hue recommendations emerging from the meeting included integrating flood risk under extreme scenarios into the urban master plan currently under development by koica development of_an electronic flood_map and_monitoring system through participatory mapping and_building awareness_and capacity of city planners to integrate climate change into planning for more information about m-brace please contact kenneth_macclune chief of_party at nghiên_cứu nguy_cơ bđkh thành_phố huế ảnh
